snippet.textDisplay: Hey Matpat, did you calculate the surface in which he is pushing the block on? You can push a couch easier on tile than you can on carpet. The mere texture of the ground can affect the friction. 5:34 is he pushing the stone on more rough sandstone, smooth tile, or is it a form of metal? Also Doesn't it also matter where he pushes the block from too? Wouldn't he need more leverage on bigger blocks because the force exerted towards the bottom is different from pushing it from the top. The way I see it he would need to lift it and push at the same time. I am not sure if that has any significance but the surface an object is on and where it is being pushed from can affect the amount of friction.
